   "source": [
    "# @title 📊 Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"BENCHMARK SUMMARY\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compare at longest sequence\n",
    "idx = -1\n",
    "print(f\"\\nAt sequence length {seq_lens[idx]}:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Forward Pass: Mamba {transformer_times[idx]/mamba_times[idx]:.2f}x faster\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Memory: Mamba uses {transformer_memory[idx]/mamba_memory[idx]:.2f}x less\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Generation: Mamba {transformer_gen_times[-1]/mamba_gen_times[-1]:.2f}x faster\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"KEY INSIGHTS\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print(\"\"\"\n",
    "1. ✅ Mamba is faster at longer sequences\n",
    "   - O(N) vs O(N²) complexity\n",
    "   - Parallel scan eliminates quadratic bottleneck\n",
    "\n",
    "2. ✅ Mamba uses less memory\n",
    "   - No attention matrix (N×N)\n",
    "   - State size is constant (d_state)\n",
    "\n",
    "3. ⚠️ Trade-offs:\n",
    "   - Transformer has full content-based access\n",
    "   - Mamba selection is learned, not explicit\n",
    "   - Transformers better at hard retrieval tasks\n",
    "\n",
    "4. 🔄 Complementary:\n",
    "   - Hybrid models (Mamba + Attention) often best\n",
    "   - Use Mamba for long contexts, attention for precision\n",
    "\"\"\")"
   ]
